TextEng: <StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> The bottom level? How many levels are there?
Text: <StartCheck>[통찰]</Start> 맨 아래층? 층이 몇 개나 돼?

TextEng: Why was the Head Gaoler torturing you?
Who's helping him?
Torture? How come?
What's the Head Gaoler up to?
What do you know about this floor of the prison?
Text: 감옥 이 층에 대해 뭘 알고 있지?

TextEng: I need you to follow me.
All right, wait here.
What da Head Guy up to?
What you know 'bout dis floor of prison?
Text: 감옥 이 층에 대해 뭐 알아?

TextEng: All right, you come wit' me.
You wait here, yuh?
Okay, enough questions about the Head Gaoler.
Okay, no more questions 'bout Head Guy, yuh?
Text: 좋아, 간수장 얘긴 더 안 물어, 응?

TextEng: Who help him?
The Pits? What are those?
Are the doors locked or unlocked?
Text: 문들은 잠겨 있어? 아니면 열려 있어?

TextEng: Where are the former prisoners holed up?
I need supplies. Are there any storerooms?
Da Pits? Ooo, what dey be?
Da doors - dey locked or unlocked?
Da prisoners - where dey hidin'?
Hmph. Der storerooms 'round here?
Yeah, I am... Get back to your cell or face the consequences.
Text: 그래, 그렇다... 당장 감방으로 돌아가, 안 그러면 대가를 치르게 될 거다.

TextEng: No, I had to fight my way through them to get here.
Text: 아니, 여기 오려면 놈들을 뚫고 와야 했어.

TextEng: ... Why do you ask?
Yeah, me prisoner. You get back to cell before you get hurts!
Text: 그래, 나 죄수. 너 다치기 전에 감방으로 돌아가!

TextEng: Me? No, me club dem on way here.
Text: 나? 아니, 오는 길에 다 패버렸지.

TextEng: Uh... Is dis a trick question?
Who are you, anyways?
How come you're not in your cell?
Think you could answer some questions for me?
Text: 내 질문 몇 가지에 답해 줄 수 있겠나?

TextEng: All right, get out of here then.
Who you be, huh?
You not in cell. How come?
Uh, me have questions. You got time?
Text: 어, 나 질문 있어. 시간 있어?

TextEng: Okay den, get out of here.
That's all I need to know about the prison.
Text: 감옥에 관해 알아야 할 건 다 알았다.

TextEng: That all me need to know 'bout prison.
